    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.14.9"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <hi rend="caps">POETRY SOCIETY OF AMERICA</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    Curtis Hidden Page, President
                    
                    <dateline>
                        454 Riverside Drive
                        New York City
                        February 9, 1929
                    </dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>The St. Louis Post-Dispatch</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis   Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>My dear Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It was good to have a note from you, and I hope that we shall note lose track of each other, but go on from the start of what I trust is a real friendship.</p>
                
                <p>Every one speaks with genuine appreciation of your readings here, and of yourself, and of your generosity in coming. So soon as I find enough leisure in this too crowded life &#8212; or else sooner &#8212; I want to read through all your longer poems, and catch up to date in your work, which I have always followed from the beginning. Then I shall want to write you again, whether a letter has come from you in the meantime, or not. One advantage in mens' friendships which I have but seldom found in the friendships of women, is that they never count up or question about an exchange of letters, but can begin over again at the same point without communications in between.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Cordially yours</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Curtis Hidden Page</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="recipient" place="left margin">after I was guest of honor for a week, of the Poetry Society.</note>
                              
            </div1>
